    <section>
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <p>
     Quantum GIS (QGIS) is designed to be a Geographic Information System (GIS) 
     built for Linux/Unix. QGIS will ultimately offer support for vector, raster,
     and database formats.
     </p>
     </section>
     <section>
     <title>Current Features</title>
     <ul>
	<li>Support for spatially enabled PostgreSQL tables using PostGIS</li> 
	<li>Support for ESRI shapefiles</li>
	<li>Identify features</li> 
	<li>Display attribute table</li> 
	<li>Select features (shapefiles only)</li>
	<li>Save projects</li>
	<li>Change symbology and layer titles</li>
	<li>Export to Mapserver map file</li>
	</ul>
 


